ds that hold the cryptocurrency was driven in part by sales of Grayscale Bi=
tcoin Trust shares, according to SkyBridge Capital founder Anthony Scaramuc=
ci.
=E2=80=9CThere seems to be of lot of selling of Grayscale,=E2=80=9D Scaramu=
cci said during a Bloomberg Television interview on Friday.
The hedge fund manager said that his trading desk noted that holders of the=
 shares, which were converted from a trust this week when the US Securities=
 and Exchange Commission signed off on the ETFs, were selling to book losse=
s and shifting to lower fee alternatives.

=E2=80=9CShifting to lower-fee=C2=A0alternatives=E2=80=9D should be neutral=
 for Bitcoin =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9CSelling one Bitcoin product to buy ano=
ther should not impact Bitcoin=E2=80=99s price, said Zach Pandl, Grayscale=
=E2=80=99s managing director or research=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0but just g=
etting out=C2=A0entirely would lower the price, and GBTC holders haven=E2=
=80=99t been able to do that for years.

