color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Bloo=
mberg=E2=80=99s Edwin Chan and Linda Lew report</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk leaned on Tesla Inc.=E2=80=99s board=
 to arrange another massive performance award for him after he sold a signi=
ficant chunk of his stake in the company to acquire Twitter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In one of several posts on the topic, Musk wro=
te that unless he has roughly 25% voting control at Tesla, he=E2=80=99d pre=
fer to build artificial intelligence and robotics products elsewhere. While=
 he remains the carmaker=E2=80=99s biggest shareholder with an almost 13% s=
take, he cashed in almost $40 billion worth of shares in 2022 to help fund =
the Twitter deal.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk, 52, praised Tesla=E2=80=99s board in oth=
er posts and said directors were waiting for a Delaware Chancery Court ruli=
ng before preparing another compensation plan. Judge Kathaleen St. J. McCor=
mick =E2=80=94 who also presided over Musk=E2=80=99s ill-fated attempt to g=
et out of the Twitter deal =E2=80=94 will decide a case brought by a Tesla =
shareholder who alleges Tesla=E2=80=99s board failed to exercise independen=
ce from Musk as it drew up his $55 billion performance award in 2018. ...</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk=E2=80=99s claim that he=E2=80=99s =E2=80=
=9Cuncomfortable growing Tesla to be a leader in AI &amp; robotics=E2=80=9D=
 follows repeated boasts over the years that the company was a leader in th=
e fields. Tesla markets products it calls Autopilot and Full Self-Driving =
=E2=80=94 both of which are driver-support features =E2=80=94 and has been =
developing a humanoid robot called Optimus. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In July of last year, Musk announced the forma=
tion of xAI, a startup that aims to rival Microsoft Corp.-backed OpenAI and=
 Google=E2=80=99s Deepmind. A week later, an analyst asked him during a Tes=
la earnings call whether the new AI company would overlap with, compete wit=
h or enhance the value of the carmaker=E2=80=99s AI efforts. He said the la=
tter.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I laid out the=C2=A0theoretical corporate fina=
nce considerations above and, sure, Tesla=E2=80=99s car factories are capit=
al-intensive while some of Musk=E2=80=99s software projects are maybe=C2=A0=
less so. But that=E2=80=99s not really what=E2=80=99s going on here. What's=
 going on here is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Musk started Tesla,<a class=3D"footno=
te-index" href=3D"#footnote-6" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: no=
ne !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bord=
er-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important;=
 display: inline-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a> raised outside money, and still owned about 20% of it.</li>=09<li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">He then=C2=A0<em>sold=C2=A0</em>a big chunk of th=
at stake to raise cash, for himself, to buy another company (Twitter)=C2=A0=
in his personal account (<em>not=C2=A0</em>for Tesla).</li>=09<li style=3D"=
margin-bottom: 5px;">Now he=E2=80=99s going back to Tesla to be like =E2=80=
=9Cwell, I own a lot of companies, and I can=E2=80=99t really give Tesla my=
 full attention while only owning 13% of it, so you=E2=80=99d better double=
 my stake, for free, if you want me to keep doing good ideas at Tesla inste=
ad of at all my other companies.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Honestly it=E2=80=99s a good threat! If you=E2=
=80=99re Tesla=E2=80=99s board, and you know that Elon Musk=E2=80=99s top p=
riority now is building AI, wouldn=E2=80=99t you rather have him do it at T=
esla than elsewhere? Presumably you want him paying attention to Tesla =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0that=E2=80=99s why you=E2=80=99ve paid him billions of dollars =
to be Tesla=E2=80=99s CEO! =E2=80=94=C2=A0so you=E2=80=99d be sad if he tur=
ned all of his attention elsewhere.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And yet there is something pretty obnoxious=C2=
=A0about it. He can keep doing this! What if you give him 25% of Tesla, he =
sells <em>that</em> stake for billions of dollars, he uses the billions of =
dollars to fund some new distracting hobby, and he comes back to you in a y=
ear saying =E2=80=9Cyeah, I don=E2=80=99t know, my heart isn=E2=80=99t real=
ly in Tesla anymore, maybe if you gave me another 25% it would motivate me.=
=E2=80=9D The $55 billion pay package in 2018 =E2=80=94=C2=A0the one that t=
he board is currently getting sued for =E2=80=94=C2=A0was supposed to motiv=
ate him to focus on Tesla, and it very clearly had the opposite effect! It =
gave him too much money, which he spent on distractions. And now he needs m=
ore money to turn back to Tesla from those distractions.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In general, with normal workers, the tension i=
s that you want to pay them enough to motivate them, but not so much that t=
hey =E2=80=9Ccall in rich=E2=80=9D and stop working. With Elon Musk, who is=
 on some days the richest man in the world, you might think this would not =
be a huge problem. You might think =E2=80=9Cwell, whatever motivated him to=
 work night and day to increase his wealth from tens of billions to=C2=A0hu=
ndreds of billions of dollars, it probably wasn't his=C2=A0<em>paycheck</em=
>, so we can rely on his intrinsic motivation to solve big problems and get=
 glory for himself.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But that is wrong: Musk has plenty of intrinsi=
c motivation, sure, but no particular reason to solve big problems=C2=A0<em=
>for Tesla</em>, as opposed to the many other companies that he has started=
 or could start. It turns out that the problem of motivation is=C2=A0<em>mu=
ch worse=C2=A0</em>for him. He=E2=80=99s got too much going on, and too muc=
h money; his companies need to compete for his attention, and that competit=
ion is expensive.</p>
