uess at the clearing price, and the most overconfident bank would win. If s=
ome bank thought =E2=80=9Cwe can sell this down $2 and only need $0.25 of p=
rofit,=E2=80=9D they=E2=80=99d bid $97.75 and win the auction; but if you p=
re-sell the stock down to $97 they=E2=80=99ll bid $94.75 and lose to your b=
id of $96.</p>
